    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-02-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="684" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <head>No. 684.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">King</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State,</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 2,
                            1887</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 187.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 277, of the 15th
                        ultimo, inclosing a copy of your note to the Sublime Porte in regard to the
                        interference with colporteurs employed by American missionaries in Turkey,
                        and have to approve your interest in the matter.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
